Adds a new `sst.cloudflare.AiSearch` component for the [AI Search Workers binding](https://developers.cloudflare.com/ai-search/api/search/workers-binding/).

Supports both binding types:
- **Instance binding** (`ai_search`) — binds to a single instance by name
- **Namespace binding** (`ai_search_namespaces`) — binds to a namespace for multi-instance access

```ts
// Instance binding
const search = new sst.cloudflare.AiSearch("MySearch", {
  instance: "my-docs-index"
});

// Namespace binding
const search = new sst.cloudflare.AiSearch("MySearch", {
  namespace: "my-namespace"
});
```

**Note:** The instance binding (`instanceName` property) requires `@pulumi/cloudflare` to bridge a Terraform provider version that includes the `instance_name` field on `WorkerScriptBinding`. The field is already in the [Terraform provider](https://github.com/cloudflare/terraform-provider-cloudflare/blob/main/internal/services/workers_script/model.go) and the [Cloudflare OpenAPI spec](https://developers.cloudflare.com/api), but hasn't been bridged to Pulumi yet. The namespace binding and `sst dev` mode work today.

Adds `sst.cloudflare.RateLimit` component using the [rate limit binding](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/runtime-apis/bindings/rate-limit/) for simple rate limiting in Cloudflare Workers.

```ts
// sst.config.ts
const rateLimit = new sst.cloudflare.RateLimit("MyRateLimit", {
  namespaceId: 1001,
  limit: 100,
  period: "1 minute",
});
```

This requires @pulumi/cloudflare minimum v6.15.0 from #6852.
